    <!-- 
    Alerts displayed in the app. Only if defined here and reported by the Coffee Machine, the Alert is displayed. 
    
    Definitions:
    Bit: The Bit representing corresponding Alert
    Name: Used for identifying the Alert in the XML File
    Title: Translation Key for Title of Alert (Int only)
    Message: Transaltion Key for Message of Alert (Int only)
    Picture: The icon displayed on the Alert
    Type: one of block, info, ip
        block = blocks all products
        info, ip = products are only blocked if specified in Blocked (see below)
    Blocked: P-Kind of blocked products: C, M, T, CM, TM, P
        CM block products of Coffe, Milk and Coffe + Milk
    CancelButton: if set, needs to be 72
    Disabled: only used on watch. Disables only certain Products and not all Products of a Kind. May be removed (using Blocked with Product Kind)
    ProcessButton: translation key for the Process Button displayed on the Alert. Needs to be one of 70, 206, 207, 208 (can be extended)
    Process: the Process to start when ProcessButton is pressed.
    ShopButton: translation key for shop button. fixed to 71 if available. Not used anymore as we do not show Shop Info on Buttons
    ShopURL: The URL to the shop with given parts? (not used anymore)

    Coloring in the App:
    Alerts with type == block are displayed in RED
    Alerts which have a blocked are displayed in YELLOW
    Alerts which have a process are displayed in BLUE
    All other Alerts are displayed in Grey/White

